To implement the “update‐README‐timestamp” feature, we need to:

1. Add the TIMESTAMP placeholder to the README.  
2. Create the update script under `scripts/`.  
3. Make it executable.  
4. Add a GitHub Actions workflow.  

Below are the exact patch(es) to apply.

---

## 1. Add placeholder to README.md

Insert the two marker lines (`<!-- TIMESTAMP:START -->` / `<!-- TIMESTAMP:END -->`) into `README.md` where you want the timestamp to appear. For example, immediately under the project title:

```diff
diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
index a1b2c3d..e4f5g6h 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ # Project Title
-# Project Title
-
-A short description of your project.
+# Project Title
+
+A short description of your project.
+
+<!-- TIMESTAMP:START -->
+<!-- TIMESTAMP:END -->
```
【F:README.md†L6-L7】

---

## 2. Create the update script

Create a new file `scripts/update-readme-timestamp.sh` (make sure the `scripts/` directory exists):

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

README="README.md"
START="<!-- TIMESTAMP:START -->"
END="<!-- TIMESTAMP:END -->"
NOW=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S %z')

# Rewrite README.md in-place, inserting the timestamp
awk -v start="$START" -v end="$END" -v now="$NOW" '
  $0 == start { print; print ""; print "更新日時: " now; print ""; in_block=1; next }
  $0 == end   { in_block=0 }
  !in_block   { print }
' "$README" > "$README.tmp" && mv "$README.tmp" "$README"
```
【F:scripts/update-readme-timestamp.sh†new】

---

## 3. Make the script executable

```bash
chmod +x scripts/update-readme-timestamp.sh
```

---

## 4. Add GitHub Actions workflow

Add `.github/workflows/update-readme.yml`:

```yaml
name: Update README Timestamp

on:
  schedule:
    - cron: '0 * * * *'      # every hour
  push:
    branches:
      - main

jobs:
  update-timestamp:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3
      - name: Update README timestamp
        run: scripts/update-readme-timestamp.sh
      - name: Commit changes
        run: |
          git config user.name "github-actions[bot]"
          git config user.email "github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com"
          git commit -am "chore: update README timestamp" || echo "No changes to commit"
      - uses: ad-m/github-push-action@v0.6.0
        with:
          github_token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
```
【F:.github/workflows/update-readme.yml†new】

---

### Final steps

```bash
git add README.md scripts/update-readme-timestamp.sh .github/workflows/update-readme.yml
git commit -m "chore: add script and workflow to auto-update README timestamp"
git push
```

---

That’s all! Once merged, your README will automatically contain an up-to-date “更新日時” timestamp.